                <img class="location-image" src="/content/images/HeartBeat_Ideation/locations/developments/IMG_1234.jpeg">
                <img class="location-image" src="/content/images/HeartBeat_Ideation/locations/developments/IMG_1236.jpeg">
            </div>
            <div class="caption">

                <p class="title" id="location-title">
                    New Developments Near Me (Around Evan's Farms)
                </p>
                <p class="description">
                    My mom and I recently moved to a developing area and I find the constant growth fascinating. Like just the phenomenon of Columbus continuing to grow and grow and grow and grow ever since I was born. There are neighborhoods, sports fields, etc. all being built and some of them offer unique landscapes. Specifically, the unpainted garages and unfinished houses (I don't technically have permission... but like no one was there at night so idk how you feel abt taking photos in them but I would be down). But also there's this like hugeee array of sports fields being built and I would love to try and take some photos under the big field lights or utilize the soccer goals that are there (a symbol of the era in my head). Also the construction cones and bright orange color was speaking to me at the moment.
                    <ul>
                        <p class="list-p">What I Like and lowkey also don't</p>
                            <li>- Development is like neverending</li>
                            <li>- Development never stops</li>
                            <li>- Everything is always developing</li>
                            <li>- Would give the pictures a unique landscape and background to work with</li>
                        <p class="list-p">What I Don't Like</p>
                            <li>- A little risky bc I don't think we're actually allowed to be there but I would still do take pics there if you would it would also be late and in the dark of night and like no one would be around and we wouldn't disturb anything</li>
                    </ul>
                </p>

