            <div class="caption">

                <p class="title" id="location-title">
                    Random Buildings & Parking Lots & Electrical Towers Near Me
                </p>
                <p class="description">
                    I drive down this road everyday so I kind of just got to a point where I imagined taking photos here. There's a small open field, a gate into an electrical tower forest, native sunscape-esque fields, empty parking lots, interesting windows on big buildings, small building strips, there was even a secret warehouse with tennis courts. This and the section above are within a minute or two of each other. At night it almost felt liminal, but it was surprisingly not vacant. Like I think some people work at night in some of these buildings.
                    <ul>
                        <p class="list-p">What I Like</p>
                            <li>- Emptiness</li>
                            <li>- It reminds me of like the outskirts of suburbia</li>
                            <li>- A lot of things to try within walking distance</li>
                        <p class="list-p">What I Don't Like</p>
                            <li>- So many things that it could take a lot of time to get through</li>
                    </ul>
                </p>

                <iframe class="location-map" src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m14!1m12!1m3!1d2214.0672273300956!2d-83.0140970632396!3d40.18794823586596!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sus!4v1779927325227!5m2!1sen!2sus" width="70vw" height="auto" style="border:0;" allowfullscreen="" loading="lazy" referrerpolicy="no-referrer-when-downgrade"></iframe>

