            </div>
            <div class="caption">

                <p class="title" id="location-title">
                    Alum Creek Dam & My Aunt's House
                </p>
                <p class="description">
                    I don't have many pics of this and also can't find any at night, but it's super pretty. You can walk above the dam and there's also a secret hammock spot that could be cool to take pics near. It's superrr pretty during the sunset. It's also right next to my aunt's house who has a cool backyard that could be a good place to take photos. Even their basement is super nice, I think I'm just personally attached to it and find it beauty in it because of that though. The photos suck but if you right click and open the image in a new tab then you can see the full images!
                    <ul>
                        <p class="list-p">What I Like</p>
                            <li>- Pretty during sunet</li>
                            <li>- Big dam infrastructure</li>
                            <li>- I love my aunt's house and yard</li>
                        <p class="list-p">What I Don't Like</p>
                            <li>- Huge amount of land, could literally take forever to get from one place to the next</li>
                    </ul>
                </p>

