        <div class="song" style="background-color: white; padding-top: 40px;">
            <p class="title" style="font-weight: bolder; font-size: 2rem; line-height: 90%">Photos of yours that I LOVE! Also some things I have that we could use, just extra inspiration</p>
            <br>
            <a href="/content/text/HeartBeat.txt" target="_blank">HeartBeat is...</a>
            <div class="two-column" id="ben">
                <div class="column-one">
                    <img src="/content/images/HeartBeat_Ideation/ben1.jpg">
                    <p class="description">I love cropped images or literal negative space added in post (used a lot of it in a <a href="https://youtu.be/ukHzCk0bxm4?si=O--TSC5qXG3A5lGT" target="_blank" class="mv">music video I made</a>), and this is stun. Although I mostly see us taking photos at night, I love lens flares and the art of suggestion. One of my only philosophies about music is that music should make the listener imagine or wonder.</p>
                    <img src="/content/images/HeartBeat_Ideation/ben2.jpg">
                    <p class="description">I mean, come on. I'm sure you already how great of an image this is. I think because of the areas I've lived, I'm drawn to suburbia's monotony and the yearning of escaping it. To me, the photo acknowledges that, but it also promises that suburbia is a perfect place to stay forever with a nice community.</p>
                    <!-- <img src="/content/images/HeartBeat_Ideation/ben3.jpg">
                    <p class="description">Classic and perfect artist picture, love the framing.</p>
                    <img src="/content/images/HeartBeat_Ideation/ben4.jpg">
                    <p class="description">I'm not opposed to things like double exposure, overlays, intentional blur, manipulation in post, literally all that is cool with me. As long as none of it is AI ofc. But I love this one specifically because it eternally traps the subject inside of technology despite them touching grass. Kinda like how I feel trapped in suburbia. But yea these are some of the coolest photos of yours, in my opinion. The talent bleeeedddss.</p> -->
                </div>
                <div class="column-two">
