                    <p class="description">Classic and perfect artist picture, love the framing.</p>
                    <img src="/content/images/HeartBeat_Ideation/ben4.jpg">
                    <p class="description">I'm not opposed to things like double exposure, overlays, intentional blur, manipulation in post, literally all that is cool with me. As long as none of it is AI ofc. But I love this one specifically because it eternally traps the subject inside of technology despite them touching grass. Kinda like how I feel trapped in suburbia. But yea these are some of the coolest photos of yours, in my opinion. The talent bleeeedddss.</p>
                    <!-- <p class="description">This second column is all photos I've taken that I think can further help with direction. I also don't want you to think I have anything that specific in mind, though. I'm open to pretty much everything and I know collaboration is a two-way street, so I wanna make sure I'm doing what I can to help.</p>
                    <img src="/content/images/frankenflower.png">
                    <p class="description">So I lied because this first one is technically, like, 10 images that I've taken, all frankensteined into one. But I love combining natural elements with digital manipulation (without AI). And I love saturation which I feel also shows throughout your work, but you do it in a cool way where it sort of selectively pops out in certain areas of grayness.</p>
                    <img src="/content/images/iam/DSCF1945.jpg">
                    <p class="description">This is moreso an opportunity showcase but I recently completed <a href="https://loveisdancing.com/iam" target="_blank" class="mv">my senior thesis</a> which was all about audio visualization and the intersection of music and visual arts. It incorporated a projector and some abstract visuals and it could be cool to play around with projections. This also isn't even my picture.</p>
                    <img src="/content/images/HeartBeat_Ideation/maxds.gif">
                    <p class="description">While looking for photos I came across the ones I took on my old DS. idk.</p>
                    <img src="/content/images/HeartBeat_Ideation/IMG_0471.JPG">
                    <p class="description">Also not my picture but I love the colors. Shoutout Trevor Paglen.</p> -->
                </div>
            </div>
            <img src="/content/images/HeartBeat_Ideation/cams.jpg" class="bottompic">
            <p class="description">I've got a small range of cameras and props we could play around with too. I love iPod photos, digicam photos, and I reallyyy wanna try film soup so that could fun to try and take some pics on film. I only have b&w film though and no flash for the camera so that could be a challenge. I have a projector that could be cool to project some things like <a href="https://loveisdancing.com/iam" target="_blank" class="mv">my senior thesis</a>.</p>
            <p class="subtext">Here's some links to my <a href="https://soundcloud.com/maxsdemos" class="mv">old SoundCloud number 1</a> and <a href="https://soundcloud.com/sketchist" class="mv">my old SoundCloud number 2</a> to get a feel for some of my older music, also <a href="https://open.spotify.com/playlist/65qg2a9wGQwQvNzglpmlYR?si=7deab8e860064318" class="mv">some more musical influence</a> if music is something that inspires your visuals.</p>
            <p class="subtext"><a href="https://www.cosmos.so/maxbass/love-is-dancing" target="_blank" class="mv">Here's a Cosmos board</a>. But as mentioned, I'm open to all ideas!</p>
